<div style="font-family: 'Calibri'; text-align: justify; font-size:
14.54px;" align="justify">Dear Sir/Ma'am,<br /><br /> Greetings from <b>IIM
Lucknow!</b><br /><br /> We are coming up with a programme on <b>" Business
Risk Management for Decision Making "</b> scheduled from <b>July 08 - 10,
2019</b> at <b>IIM Lucknow.</b><br /><br /> <b>OBJECTIVES :</b><br />
Business organizations are impacted by risks of all kinds &ndash; market
risk, manufacturing risk, new product or service introduction risk, project
risks, risks arising from competitor activities, key personnel attrition
risk, credit risk, operational risk, etc. Many of these risks can have a
severe negative impact on the business, and may even threaten its
existence. The programme         broadly covers essential elements of risk
measurement and management techniques for market risk, credit risk,
operational risk, and liquidity risk.<br /><br /> <b>CONTENTS</b>
<ul style="margin-top: 0px;">
<li> Understanding various business risk, Basic risk types, measurement and
management tools, Evaluation of Business Risk for Decision Making -Creating
value with risk management </li>
<li> The framework of Risk Management and Decision Making </li>
<li> Risk Analytics, Risk-adjusted performance measurement case for
Performance Risk Management. </li>
<li> Probabilistic Approaches: Scenario Analysis, Decision Tree,
Simulations </li>
</ul>
<b>Programme Directors:</b> Prof. Vikas Srivastava &amp; Prof. Seshadev
Sahoo<br /><br /> <b>METHODOLOGY :</b><br /> The programme will be
conducted through the combination of lectures, experience sharing, case
studies, and role playing and in an interactive workshop mode.<br /><br />
<b>Participant Profile:</b><br /> The programme will benefit for Financial
analysis, bank executives, consultants and professional members engaged in
investment advisory services and Middle and Top-level managers taking
strategic decisions about portfolio management and investment fund managers
Financial analysis, bank executives.<br /><br /> <b><u>How to
apply:</u></b> <ol style="margin-top: 0px;">
